    Description

    The drum is a member of the percussion group of musical instruments. In the Hornbostel-Sachs classification system, it is a membranophone. Wikipedia
    Related instruments: Drum Kit, Taiko, Snare drum, Bass drum, MORE
    Type of instrument
    What type of instrument is a drum?
    percussion instruments
    Drums are percussion instruments that make sound when a player strikes a drum head—a stretched membrane attached to the instrument's frame or drum shell. This makes drums a type of membranophone.Jun 7, 2021

    How to clean
    how to clean drum
    Household cleaners and polishes like Pledge can work well, too. You can also use some household items such as vinegar or dish soap. You should mix it with water, and clean the drums gently with a lint-free cloth. Take care to dry all drum parts after the cleaning!
